cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper is about computer vision neural networks, specifically MobileNets, and their compression through quantization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the design and organization of resource-efficient architectures, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel quantization method, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions specialized hardware such as ASICs and FPGAs, which is relevant to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
